Rift Valley fever, Namibia
---------------------------
Information received on 14 May 2010 from Dr Albertina Shilongo, Chief
Veterinarian Epidemiology, Import and Export Control and Training,
Directorate of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Water &
Forestry, Windhoek, Namibia

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 10 May 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 12 May 2010
Report date: 14 May 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 14 May 2010
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: May 1985
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Rift Valley fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Location: HARDAP (Hebron No 493, Mariental)
Total animals affected:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Sheep/ 3300/ 10/ 7/ 3/ 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors
Control measures
Measures applied: Quarantine, Movement control inside the country, No
vaccination [Why? - Mod.AS], No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Control of arthropods, Vaccination in
response to the outbreak.

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory, Windhoek
(National laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Sheep/ real-time PCR/ 12 May 2010/ Positive

